                "SISD",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Reaction products were detected by",
                "two similar telescope detectors. Each telesccope",
                "included double sided Si strip detector with",
                "thickness of 20 mu-m backed by a Si pad detector 150",
                "mu-m thick. One telescope covered an angular range",
                "between 25.8deg and 69.2deg on the left side and",
                "second telescope covered an angular range between",
                "28.5deg and 66.5deg on the right side"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight (TOF) was used to discriminate",
                "between secondary beams 8B and 7Be. Tof was started by",
                "rf timing pulse from beam buncher and stopped by dE",
                "detector of both telescopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Primary bunched beam of 6Li with energy of 37 MeV",
                "impinged on a 3He gas target. The reaction products",
                "included in the secondary beam were 7Li at 13.1 MeV,",
                "7Be at 22.4 MeV and 8B at the energy of 30.5 MeV. The",
                "secondary beams and part of the scattered primary 6Li",
                "beam were transported via TwinSol to reaction target."
              ]
            }
          ],
